{"word":"ὑλήεις","slug":"ὑλήεις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑλήεις</b></el> <el>(ὑλήεις, εσσα, εν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὕλη'><el>ὕλη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>woody, wooded</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἀταρπὸς ὑλ.</el> a path <i>through the wood</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>dwelling in the woods</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}